SEARCH
Package fitnessclub

Class StudioManager

java.lang.Object
fitnessclub.StudioManager
public class StudioManager extends Object
User Interface for software that manages a fitness club. Allows members to be added/removed from the database, for them or guest to attend/be removed from classes and has several options for printing club information to console. Interface is interactive and terminal based.
Author:
Ashley Berlinski

    • checkClass

      private boolean checkClass(Member member, FitnessClass fitnessClass, boolean isGuest)
      Checks various conditions that could prevent a member from attending a class. Check if guest is allowed to attend, if member/guest can go to class or if there is a time conflict.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that is being checked.
      fitnessClass - the fitness class the member is attempting to attend.
      isGuest - flag used to indicate if member being added to class is a guest.
      Returns:
      true if the member can attend the given fitness class, false if otherwise.

    • timeConflictOrInClass

      private boolean timeConflictOrInClass(FitnessClass fitnessClass, FitnessClass[] sameTimeClass, Member member, boolean adding, boolean isGuest)
      Checks if a member is attending a class at the same time as the requested one or is in that class already. Guests are not checked for time conflicts and an error message is only printed when trying to add a member to a class they are already in.
      Parameters:
      fitnessClass - the fitness class that is being compared.
      sameTimeClass - fitness classes that are being offered at the same time of day.
      member - the member that is being checked.
      adding - flag used to indicate if a member is trying to be added to the class.
      isGuest - flag used to indicate if a guest is trying to be added to the class.
      Returns:
      true if member is in class, if adding and not guest true if there is a conflict, false otherwise.

    • getFitnessClass

      private FitnessClass getFitnessClass()
      Determines if the given tokens can create a valid fitness class. If the class offered, studio location or instructor does not exist then no class will be returned.
      Returns:
      a fitness class object if one could be created, null if one of the tokens was invalid.

    • isValidProfile

      private boolean isValidProfile(Profile profile)
      Check if profile given is valid, will reject profiles that have an invalid DOB
      Parameters:
      profile - the profile being checked.
      Returns:
      true if the profile is valid, false if otherwise.

    • isValidMember

      private boolean isValidMember(Profile profile, Member member)
      Checks if a member is a valid member in the database. Members are invalid if they are not in the database or if their membership has expired.
      Parameters:
      profile - the profile of the member being searched for.
      member - the member that was matched to the profile given.
      Returns:
      true if the member is a valid one, false if otherwise.

    • isValidDOB

      private boolean isValidDOB(Date dob)
      Checks if the member's DOB is valid. Dates are not valid if they are improperly formatted, are from today/future date, if they are not a valid calendar date, or if the member is not an adult.
      Parameters:
      dob - the date of birth being checked.
      Returns:
      true if the DOB is valid, false if otherwise.

    • isValidClass

      private boolean isValidClass(Offer offerClass)
      Checks if a given Offer object is an offered class.
      Parameters:
      offerClass - the class that is being checked.
      Returns:
      true if the class is being offered, false if otherwise.

    • isFitnessClassOnSchedule

      private boolean isFitnessClassOnSchedule(FitnessClass fitnessClass)
      Checks if fitness class was on the schedule.
      Parameters:
      fitnessClass - the fitness class being checked.
      Returns:
      true if the fitness class was on the schedule, false if otherwise.

    • isValidInstructor

      private boolean isValidInstructor(Instructor instructor)
      Checks if a given Instructor object is an existing instructor.
      Parameters:
      instructor - the instructor being checked.
      Returns:
      true if the instructor exists, false if otherwise.

    • isValidStudio

      private boolean isValidStudio(Location studio, boolean addingMember)
      Checks if a given Location object is a valid studio.
      Parameters:
      studio - the studio that is being checked.
      addingMember - flag used to indicate where the studio token will be for different commands (add/attend)
      Returns:
      true if the location is a valid studio, false otherwise.

    • isValidGuest

      private boolean isValidGuest(Member member, Location studio)
      Checks if member is allowed to have a guest attend a class. Basic members are not allowed guests, and other members must have available guest passes and guests can only attend classes in their home studio.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that is being checked.
      Returns:
      true if the member meets the requirements for a guest to attend, false if otherwise.

    • canGoToClass

      private boolean canGoToClass(Member member, FitnessClass fitnessClass)
      Checks if member is allowed to go to class, provided their membership type and class location. If the member is a basic member they can only attend classes at their home studio.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that is being checked.
      fitnessClass - the fitness class that is being requested to attend.
      Returns:
      true if the member is allowed to attend, false if otherwise.

    • enoughTokens

      private boolean enoughTokens(int lastTokenIndex)
      Checks if user has input enough tokens for the associated command
      Parameters:
      lastTokenIndex - the index of the last token needed for the command.
      Returns:
      true if there were enough tokens provided, false otherwise

    • printLoadedContent

      private void printLoadedContent()
      Prints the contents of the members list and schedule, having read from the associated files.

    • run

      public void run()
      Method which runs the studio manager on the console. Program will terminate when user inputs the quit command.
